# Gunner — Cursor Rules

## Branch
Always work on the active deploy branch. Never commit to `main`.

## Stack
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite (client/src/)
- Backend: Node.js + Express + tRPC (server/)
- DB: PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM — schema in drizzle/schema.ts
- Storage: Supabase Storage (gunner-recordings bucket)
- Deploy: Railway — auto-deploys on push to active branch

## Active Tenants
- ID=1: New Again Houses (primary, live)
- ID=450029: NAH Kitty Hawk (onboarding soon)
- ID=540044: Apex Property Solutions (demo)
- Never hardcode tenantId — always multi-tenant safe

## Env Vars
All secrets live in Railway env vars. Access via ENV object in server/_core/env.ts.
Never use raw process.env in business logic. Never hardcode keys.

## Before Every Push
1. `npx tsc --noEmit` → must be 0 errors
2. Commit with prefix: fix: / feat: / docs: / refactor:
3. Push to the active deploy branch only

## Key Files
- server/_core/env.ts — all environment variables
- server/routers.ts — all API endpoints
- drizzle/schema.ts — database schema (source of truth)
- server/_core/llm.ts — AI/LLM calls (OpenAI)
- server/_core/voiceTranscription.ts — Whisper transcription
- server/storage.ts — Supabase file storage
- server/emailService.ts — Resend email sending
- server/ghlService.ts — GHL CRM sync

